<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p> <rs type="material" key="marmor">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType" reg="statue base">statue base</rs> upper plinth, with moulding on three sides and roughed out, but not completed, on the back (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width" precision="circa">0.36</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height" precision="circa">1.20</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth" precision="circa">1.03</measure>) There is a clamp hole on the underside for an  attachment; the top is not currently visible.    The plinth supported the statue of Aphrodite now in the Aphrodisias Museum.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the lower <term>fascia</term> (<measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre">0.865</measure>   × <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.085</measure>). The stone is complete except for chipping at the upper right corner and along edges; the text must have been completed on a lower feature.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p>well-cut, with elaborate serifs; <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.075</measure></p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p><date notBefore="0167" notAfter="0233" exact="none" cert="low">Late second to early third centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>).</p>
</div>

<div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/><w lemma="θεά">θεὰν</w>  <persName full="yes" type="divine"><name>Ἀφροδεί<lb n="1a" type="worddiv"/><supplied reason="lost">ταν</supplied></name></persName>  <gap reason="lost" dim="right" unit="character" extent="unknown"/></ab>
</div>

